The article discusses the upcoming one-year anniversary of Russia's invasion of Ukraine and the US's commitment to supporting Ukraine's democracy, sovereignty, and territorial integrity. The author, who is in Kyiv to meet with President Zelenskyy, emphasizes that Putin was wrong in thinking Ukraine was weak and the West was divided. The author announces the delivery of critical equipment to help protect the Ukrainian people and the imposition of additional sanctions against individuals and companies supporting Russia's war machine. The United States has built a coalition of nations to support Ukraine, and this support will continue. The author also plans to meet with the leaders of Eastern Flank Allies and deliver remarks on rallying global support for Ukraine and human rights.